725795f-a.text:
111th Street, west side, north from and across 53rd Avenue. Public School No. 1V can be seen at 52nd Street [sic, actually 52nd Avenue]. The east side of the street is now part of the World's Fair
gounds and Flushing Meadow Park.
P. L. Sperr  June 23, 1940

726682f-b.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (2ueens): Part of the World's Fair grounds on the east side of 111th Street and 53rd Avenue, viewing northeastward and showing, under construction, the South Corona gate and the Chrysler Motors Building. The North Corona
gate, at 50th Avenue, is or the extreme left.
View 2 shows the South Corona gate when completed; view 3, the same site as that in view 1, two years later.
View 1: May 30, 1938
View 2: Joly 12, 1939
View 3: June 23, 1940
P. L. Sperr
